    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dd562517_d9aea0aa",
        "filename": "golden/go/expstorage/types.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 61,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-15T00:01:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I recommend calling this GarbageCollector, or perhaps LRUGarbageCollector.\n\nRationale:\n- expstorage.Cleaner is probably too ambiguous.\n- \"garbage collector\" has a clear meaning for most programmers and seems to describe this interface well (modulo the \"LRU\" aspect - point in favor for LRUGarbageCollector).\n- This naming recommendation, along with the recommendations below, make this abstraction less leaky.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 61,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 61,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "dce10d223b35ebe2caab71080d40aca46e1fb49d",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a02033ca_5f52f384",
        "filename": "golden/go/expstorage/types.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 65,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-15T00:01:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Please name this \"UpdateLastUsed\".\n\nRationale: \"SetUsed\" sounds like it will set a \"used\" boolean field to true, when in reality it will update the last_used field of the FS entry, so \"UpdateLastUsed\" makes more sense.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 65,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 65,
        "endChar": 8
      },
      "revId": "dce10d223b35ebe2caab71080d40aca46e1fb49d",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "60fc41e7_3e7f02c5",
        "filename": "golden/go/expstorage/types.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 65,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-15T00:01:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think Delta is being misused here. What we want is an array of expectation \"IDs\".\n\nHow about we split the Delta struct into two structs ExpectationID and Delta? E.g.:\n\n  // Before.\n  type Delta struct {\n    Grouping types.TestName\n    Digest   types.Digest\n    Label    expectations.Label\n  }\n\n  // After.\n  type ExpectationID struct {  // Or maybe just \"ID\" (i.e. expstorage.ID).\n    Grouping types.TestName\n    Digest   types.Digest\t\n  }\n  type Delta struct {\n    ExpectationID\n    Label expectations.Label\n  }\n\nWDYT?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 65,
        "startChar": 28,
        "endLine": 65,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "dce10d223b35ebe2caab71080d40aca46e1fb49d",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c4e8f9b4_f88eec2a",
        "filename": "golden/go/expstorage/types.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-15T00:01:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I recommend naming this \"MarkUnusedEntriesForGC\", or \"MarkLRUEntriesForGC\", or maybe just \"MarkEntriesForGC\".\n\nRationale: it would make this abstraction less leaky (no need to leak the concept of an untriaged entry).\n\nIf you don\u0027t like the \"garbage collector\" idea, I suggest \"UntriageUnusedEntries\" or \"UntriageLRUEntries\" as it\u0027s more accurate; the word \"old\" in \"UntriageOldEntries\" suggests this will look at the record\u0027s age when it actually looks at field last_used.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 70,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 70,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "dce10d223b35ebe2caab71080d40aca46e1fb49d",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9c53c5d6_1e9e9e36",
        "filename": "golden/go/expstorage/types.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 78,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-15T00:01:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suggest naming this GarbageCollect().\n\nRationale:\n- Consistent with the story told by the interface as per my recommendations above.\n- Abstraction less leaky: focuses on garbage collection rather than untriaged entries.\n- It would be in line with https://golang.org/doc/effective_go.html#interface-names (even though this is not a one-method interface).\n\nIf you don\u0027t like the \"garbage collector\" idea, then please use \"Delete\" instead of \"Prune\", as the latter gives the false impression that this is some kind of tree or graph structure.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 78,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 78,
        "endChar": 22
      },
